  "description": "A resting-state EEG dataset comprising 149 subjects (100 with Parkinson's disease and 49 healthy controls) recorded using a 64-channel BrainVision system. Participants were seated in a quiet environment with eyes open for two minutes. This dataset provides neurophysiological data suitable for investigating EEG biomarkers associated with Parkinson's disease.",
  "methods_description": "Resting-state EEG was recorded using a 64-channel BrainVision cap from subjects seated in a quiet room with eyes open for two minutes. The dataset includes 100 individuals with Parkinson's disease and 49 healthy controls.",
